[SetUp "1"]

1... --
{ What you see here is a standard position in the Colorado Gambit. Although White has given up the bishop pair, he is utterly dominating on the dark-squares and Black has unspeakably bad weaknesses on c6 & e6. Even if Black gets in c5, I think both of White's minor pieces will be stronger than Black's light-squared because they will always be able to access the hole on e5. Black does not have the same luxury on the e4 square because White can play f3. }
