[Black "Latvian Gambit 2"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 f5
{ The Latvian Gambit, a waste bin opening since it was popularized long ago. }
3. Nxe5
{ White grabs the central pawn. White has tried a million different moves vs the Latvian and this is the easiest one to play. }
3... Qf6 { This move is surprisingly the mainline. } 4. Nc4
{ White can try d4 as well, but I like the systems without d4 and with an early d3 instead to remove the pawn that will appear on e4 after fxe4. }
4... Qe6
{ Another try of black's. Don't think hard here. Just develop and open the position. }
5. Nc3 fxe4 6. Ne3 c6 7. d3 d5 8. dxe4 dxe4 9. Bc4
{ Lehtinen, Pentti - Strange, Mikkel, 1-0, WS/M/114, 2007, Is completely crushing for white. }
