[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "2. 1.e4 openings"]
[Black "Damiano Defense 1"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 f6
{ The Damiano defense: one of the worst chess openings possible. White has many moves that are objectively great; I like the forcing Nxe5 the most. }
3. Nxe5
{ Grabbing the pawn is the most forcing and powerful move. d4, Bc4 are both good as well. }
3... Qe7
{ This move avoids the king hunt, but Black's development is so poor that I think its overall not much better in comparison. }
4. Nf3 d5
{ This looks like it wins the pawn back for Black, but at what cost? } 5. d3
dxe4 6. dxe4 Qxe4+ 7. Be2 Bd6 8. O-O Ne7 9. Nc3
{ Black's development is very poor and f6 is such a lemon move to have here. Bc4-Nb5 loom as well. }
*

