[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "2. 1.e4 openings"]
[Black "Damiano Defense 4"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 f6
{ The Damiano defense: one of the worst chess openings possible. White has many moves that are objectively great; I like the forcing Nxe5 the most. }
3. Nxe5
{ Grabbing the pawn is the most forcing and powerful move. d4, Bc4 are both good as well. }
3... fxe5
{ Black could play Qe7, but it leads to positions where Black is very far behind in development. Still, it's better than allowing the famous mainline here. }
4. Qh5+ { The justification of Nxe5. } 4... Ke7
{ g6 is no better than the mainline. } 5. Qxe5+
{ There's nothing easier than taking a free pawn with check. } 5... Kf7
{ Only move. } 6. Bc4+
{ This is White's best move. All other moves are inferior or do not make progress. }
6... Kg6 { Loses easily to: } 7. Qf5+ Kh6 8. h4 { d4+ is the end. } 8... Qe7 9.
d4+ g5 10. Bxg5+ { We win the queen and will mate soon. } *

