[White "2. 1.e4 openings"]
[Black "Colorado Gambit 1"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 Nc6 2. Nf3 f5
{ The Colorado Gambit, a gambit so ugly only your mother could love it. } 3.
exf5 d5 { Black tries to retain the pawn with Bxf5. } 4. Bb5
{ The simplest move as it develops the bishop to an active square. } 4... Bxf5
5. Ne5 { Threatening   6.Bxc6  bxc6  which would wreck Black's structure. }
5... a6 { Black has also tried this move, but admittedly is not that great. }
6. Bxc6+ bxc6 7. d4 e6 8. Qh5+ g6 9. Qe2 h5
{ Black should prevent g4  (winning the bishop)  . } 10. O-O
{ Black's entire structure is the weakest one I have ever seen. There is no way White is not winning. }
