1. e4 e5 2. Qh5 { The Wayward Queen Attack/Parham Opening. } 2... Nc6
{ This is the mainline of the Parham, but Nf6 is also a viable move as it a pawn sacrifice that aims to take advantage of black's development. }
3. Bc4
{ Attacking f7. White threatens the gimmicky Scholar's mate. I fell for this a few times when I was younger. }
3... g6 { Kicking the Queen away. } 4. Qf3 Nf6 { Developing. } 5. Ne2 Bg7
{ Developing. } 6. Nbc3
{ White also plays this natural developing move. A sample continuation might be: }
6... d6 7. d3 O-O 8. a3 Bg4 9. Qg3 Be6 10. Bxe6 fxe6
{ When I prefer black a bit. } *

