{ At least with this move, Black tries to trade queens. Alas, they get their wish, but the position is no bueno. }
8. Qxd4 exd4 9. g3 { Developing the kingside in an orderly fashion. } 9... Bc5
{ Developing moves make sense, but White is doing well after a line like: } 10.
Bg2 Nge7 11. Nh3
{ The knight is better placed on h3 since it can later go to f4. Meanwhile, Nf3 would have blocked the bishop on g2 and it's unclear where it would go afterward. }
11... O-O 12. Nf4
{ Followed by castles and White has the bishop pair for no compensation. } *

