1. g4 { The Grob's opening. One of Chess's most memified openings. } 1... e5
{ I like this simple pawn thrust. 1..d5 is good too. } 2. Bg2
{ White develops his bishop to g2 to make use of the g2 square. Otherwise, what was the point of 1. g4 ? }
2... d5
{ Ne7  (planning Ng6-Nh4 which is really annoying for White)  and h5 are fine moves, but I like the simple pawn thrust. }
3. c4
{ This pawn break isn't that great. Black is also doing well after 3...d4, but capturing this pawn is the simplest. }
3... dxc4 4. Qa4+ c6 5. Qxc4 Be6
{ Gives black an easy game. Just develop your pieces to good squares  (Nd7-Ngf6/Ne7-Be7/Bd6. White has only made his position look foolish with the g4 move.) }
